> Because each action is related to specific keys, it's hard to control and manage everything in a single EventRewriter.

I don't think it's difficult to create a one-instance-per-window EventRewriter for touch injector / input overlay (say, TouchInjectorEventRewriter). In pseudocode, the implementation would be like:

    class TouchInjectorEventRewriter {
     public:
      EventDispatchDetails RewriteEvent(event) override {
        for (action : actions_) {
          if (action.Match(event)) {
            action.Rewrite(event);
            return;
          }
        }
      }

      // logic to add / remove TouchInjectorEventRewriter to corresponding aura::Window here

     private:
      vector<Action> actions_;
    }

With that, EventRewriter registration / removal from a window is more readable, it's less error-prone and also we don't have to think about performance implications of having too many EventRewriters registered to each window.

