Regarding your statement above:

> So AVD will trigger the resolution change after reset.

Hmm, actually, the AVD is not obligated to trigger a resolution change after calling Reset() on it.

Let's say for example that the video changes from 320x240 to 640x360 but before OnChangeResolutionDone() is called, we get a Reset() -- so, |pic_size_| is still 320x240. Assume that this Reset() happens because we're seeking to another place in the video that's 640x360. The AVD won't trigger a resolution change after the Reset().

We may be ok though: I see that V4L2VideoDecoder::Reset() calls V4L2StatelessVideoDecoderBackend::ClearPendingRequests() which re-creates the AVD in case we're in the middle of a resolution change. The only thing that I'm uncertain about is that there's a potential early-out before calling ClearPendingRequests():

  if (state_ == State::kInitialized) {
    std::move(trampoline_reset_cb).Run();
    return;
  }

And I don't know if this early-out can be hit when OnChangeResolutionDone() is called with kAborted.

